## 2. Key Code Standards (Summary)
- **Tech Stack:** React 19, TypeScript (strict mode), MapLibre GL, TailwindCSS v4.
- **Naming Conventions:** Kebab-case folders, PascalCase components, camelCase variables & helper functions.
- **TypeScript:** Strict type-safety. Never use `any`. Use `interface` for entity structures, `type` for unions/aliases.
- **React Performance:** Memoize heavy map components using `React.memo`, utilize `useMemo` and `useCallback` to avoid unnecessary re-renders. Always cleanup event listeners on map unmount.
- **Styling:** Use TailwindCSS v4 utility classes. Manage dynamic styles using `cn(...)` wrapper (`clsx` + `tailwind-merge`).
- **Git Commit Standard:** Use Conventional Commits (`feat(scope): ...`, `fix(scope): ...`).

## 3. Testing Requirements
- Unit/Integration test coverage target: **≥ 80%** (via Vitest + React Testing Library).
- Mock maplibre-gl in tests properly (see [TEST_RULES.md](file:///Users/hienhao/Code/Home/Project/camera-map-demo/docs/rules/TEST_RULES.md#31-unit-testing) for setup examples).
- Do not skip tests for helper functions or key components.
